Add your ActiveRecord models here.

You can create them by being in the application root directory and running, e.g.,

rake generate:model NAME=User

Notes on the ActiveRecord associations:
> Menu.create({name: "Snack"})
> Item.create({name: "Coffee", price: "$1.95"})
> mmenu = Menu.last
> mitem = Item.last
> mmenu.items << mitem
> Menitem.all

1.9.3-p374 :030 > Menitem.all
D, [2013-11-17T18:26:16.477497 #87231] DEBUG -- :   Menitem Load (0.7ms)  SELECT "menitems".* FROM "menitems" 
 => [#<Menitem id: 1, menu_id: 2, item_id: 2, created_at: "2013-11-17 18:22:11", updated_at: "2013-11-17 18:22:11">] 

Only creates the cookie, not the menitem: 
 > Menu.create({name: "Snack"}).items << Item.create({name: "cookie", price: "free"})

Create the cookie first: 
=> still doesn't create the menitem

To create the join record, need to have the object for each and then:

> a_menu = Menu.last
> an_item = Item.last
> a_menu.items << an_item 

<% @the_menu_record[0].items.each do |item| %>
  <%= item.name %>
  <%= item.price %>
<% end %>